abstract: In their boisterous presidential debate, several Democrats sold short the health care plans of rivals or glossed over aspects of their own record. In an audacious league of his own, President Donald Trump celebrated the elimination of a tax that still exists and went deep and wide in distorting what he's done in office.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In their boisterous presidential debate, several Democrats sold short the health care plans of rivals or glossed over aspects of their own record. In an audacious league of his own, President Donald Trump celebrated the elimination of a tax that still exists and went deep and wide in distorting what he's done in office.
headline_main: AP FACT CHECK: Donald Trump and the Audacity of Hype

abstract: Who's got the goods on health care policy? That question was an undercurrent in the feisty Democratic presidential debate as rivals stood accused of being lightweights who have done little more than put up Post-it notes or slideshows on the subject.

abstract: Amy Eileen Haidinger, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Robert N. Haidinger of Riverside, Conn., was married there yesterday to Walter McNeill Rand, son of Mrs. Stanley Rand Jr. of Riverside and the late Mr. Rand.

abstract: Eddie Belmonte, one of the most successful riders of the late 1960's, was suspended yesterday as a jockey agent by the New York State Racing and Wagering Board in an outgrowth of the board's investigation into race-fixing.

abstract: In one important respect, European bridge organizers are ahead of their colleagues on this side of the Atlantic: They make considerable efforts to encourage young players to take up the game. In Sweden and the Netherlands, bridge is taught in schools with the aid of Government subsidies.
